<paragraph id="8BC236D91C50A359FF05A209AAEE8946" blockId="13.[151,684,1612,1669]" lastBlockId="13.[714,1247,1397,1669]" pageId="13" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D5A1C50A359FF05A209A839890A" box="[177,346,1612,1637]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Brexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="B909EACB1C50A359FF05A209A839890A" box="[177,346,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="80">Brexia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a shrub to slender treelet in subhumid forest between 1100 and 
<quantity id="4C859B3C1C50A359FD92A22EAB1E89EB" box="[550,637,1642,1669]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" unit="m" value="1600.0">1600 m</quantity>
ele- vation, from north of Moramanga to Zahamena PN/RNI and west to the Tampoketsa d’Ankazobe (Fig. 4). It can be recognized by its pseudoumbellate inflorescences borne on slender peduncles to at most 
<quantity id="4C859B3C1C50A359FC0BA1B4AD7B8965" box="[959,1048,1520,1547]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
broad, and small flowers and fruits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236D91C50A35AFD50A26BA8638F8B" blockId="13.[714,1247,1397,1669]" lastBlockId="14.[151,684,170,228]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="13" pageNumber="80">
Of the 
<specimenCount id="9D7BFD501C50A359FC83A26BAAB08928" box="[823,979,1581,1608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">three syntypes</specimenCount>
